 What Where Find Jobs Advanced Job Search Director of IT Credit Union of Colorado 44 reviews Centennial, CO 80111 Credit Union of Colorado 44 reviews Read what people are saying about working here. Job details Salary $136,100 - $180,000 a year Job Type Full-time Full Job Description General Purpose of the Position 
 
The Information Technology (IT) department is responsible for delivering and supporting infrastructure (network/compute/storage/virtualization/cloud) services, end user services, enterprise applications, application development, building integrations, service delivery and leading the adoption of artificial intelligence/machine learning (AI/ML) strategies. The Director of IT must have a strong customer service orientation and continuous improvement mindset, be a proven decision maker showing quality judgement, and work seamlessly with their team, vendors and business partners. This role will be process oriented, strategic and be capable of handling multiple priorities concurrently in a fast-paced environment. The position will utilize a strong background in IT service, project and agile release management. 
Demonstrating the strong culture of collaboration with our business partners and stakeholders this role will architect and deliver meaningful solutions and services for the credit union. The individual hired for this role will work directly with leadership on the strategy and planning of projects, application implementation and support while applying a member focused, collaborative and consultative approach to delivering IT services. 
ESSENTIAL DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES  include the following. May perform other duties as requested or assigned. 
 Lead Application Services, Application Development, IT Infrastructure services, End User services and Service Delivery functions. Provide guidance to members of the team by communicating job expectations; planning, monitoring, and appraising job results; coaching, counseling, and mentoring employees; initiating, coordinating, and enforcing systems, policies, and procedures. 
Influence senior business and technology stakeholders across the credit union. 
Establish and maintain regular written and in-person communications with the organizationâ€™s executives, decision-makers, stakeholders, department heads, and end users regarding pertinent systems architecture opportunities and activities. 
Influences and provides escalation for Enterprise Application Services and Infrastructure & End User Services leaders. 
Explain highly technical solutions to non-technical staff, crisp clear communication and ability to explain solutions and how they provide value. 
Provide architectural guidance to the Service Delivery and Project teams. 
Seeks out and evangelizes Fintech partnerships that will help deliver on Credit Union strategic initiatives. 
Direct development of complex enviromental integrations, web services and application programable interfaces (APIs). 
Guide supporting IT functions including IT project management, capacity and demand management, and asset management. 
Thought leadership on the major shifts in the technology industry such as digital transformation. 
Responsible for the management and evaluation of 3rd parties/vendors to ensure strong relationships that provide partnerships and continuous growth. 
Develop extensive knowledge and drive internal awareness to the AI/ML applications and partner ecosystems 
Participate in data governance and management functions to guide credit union data management strategies. 
Manage costs, controls and spend in relation to budgeting enterprise applications, including cloud subscriptions and technical support, education and training. 
Monitors effectiveness of existing enterprise applications and infrastructure. Provides recommendations to leadership for improved operations, systems, and updated hardware. 
Ensures that all software and platforms are up to date on newest releases, updates and patches. 
Promotes and enables training opportunities and education for team. Conducts training sessions as appropriate. 
Participate in the creation of strategies and policies to meet overall business goals. 
Professionally represents the Credit Union in contacts with business and trade professionals. 
Timely communication and issue escalation ensuring appropriate and accurate visibility to all levels of stakeholders, including senior management team. Responsible for Incident and event reporting and dashboards. 
Adhere to all Federal and State laws and regulations applicable to the credit union, including the Bank Secrecy Act and OFAC. 
Responsible for compliance with the Fair and Accurate Credit Transaction Act (FACTA), the Bank Secrecy Act (BSA) and the Anti Money Laundering Act, including monitoring for such illegal activity as it applies to this position. 
