EDUCATION AND EXPERIENCE:
 Bachelorâ€™s degree (B.A.) from four-year college or university or four years related experience and/or training; or any combination of experience and/or training equivalent to bachelorâ€™s degree in a related field.
 Minimum of eight (8) years of experience in an information technology environment, preferably in financial services.
 Minimum of four(4) years leading technical teams, guiding project implementations and delivering technology services. 
Exceptional customer/member service skills.
 Demonstrated Technical skills in complex, highly available, secure networks and infrastructure.
 Exemplary technical and business assessment skills to evaluate strategic value of technology systems, data solutions and work processes to serve members and employees. 
